This collection consists of published texts of speeches drafted by Mr. Glick and delivered by members of the Truman and Eisenhower presidential administrations, from 1951 to 1960. Texts include: opening speech
to the Democratic national campaign (1960), given by then Senator Lyndon B. Johnson; "Morals and power" speech given by Secretary of State John F. Dulles to the graduating class of the National War College (1953);
and other speeches by various ambassadors and Congressmen. "In most cases," wrote Mr. Glick concerning this collection, "the speech texts were the product of discussion between the speaker and the writer."
